SIMPLE: treasurer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Treasurer
<hw>Treas"ur*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>tresourer</ets>, F. <ets>tr⟦eacute⟧sorier</ets>.]</ety> <def>One
who has the care of a treasure or treasure or treasury; an officer who
receives the public money arising from taxes and duties, or other
sources of revenue, takes charge of the same, and disburses it upon
orders made by the proper authority; one who has charge of collected
funds; <as>as, the <ex>treasurer</ex> of a society or
corporation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lord high treasurer of England</b></col>, <cd>formerly,
the third great officer of the crown. His office is now executed by five
persons styled the <xex>lords commissioners of the treasury</xex>, or
<xex>treasury lords</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Treasurership</ent>⟦br⟧
